6 Sec. 2. 20 V.S.A. chapter 193, subchapter 7 is added to read:
7 Subchapter 7. Damages by Domestic Dogs
8 § 3821. CIVIL LIABILITY FOR INJURY CAUSED BY DOMESTIC DOGS
9 (a) Strict liability. The owner of a domestic dog has a duty to keep that dog
10 under reasonable control at all times and to keep that dog from running at
11 large. The owner may be held liable for any injury caused by the dog
12 regardless of whether the dog has shown any dangerous propensities or
13 whether the owner knew or should have known of the dog’s dangerous
14 propensities. A person who breaches the duty imposed by this section shall be
15 subject to civil liability for any damages suffered by a person who is injured by
16 the dog or whose domestic pet is injured by the dog while in a public place or
17 lawfully in or on the private property of another.
18 (b) Limitations on liability. Subsection (a) of this section shall not be
19 construed to impose liability upon:
20 (1) any governmental agency using a dog in military or police work if
21 the injury occurred during the course of the dog’s official duties; or
