2 (A) the injured person was trespassing upon the private property of
3 the dog’s owner;
4 (B) the injury occurred while the dog was protecting the dog’s owner
5 or another innocent party from attack by the injured person or a dog owned by
6 the injured person;
7 (C) the injury occurred while the dog was securely confined in a
8 kennel, a crate, or another enclosure; or
9 (D) the injury occurred as a result of the injured person enticing,
10 disturbing, alarming, harassing, or otherwise provoking the dog.
11 (c) Definitions. As used in this section:
12 (1) “Domestic pet” has the same meaning as in section 3541 of this title.
13 (2) “Owner” means a person who, at the time of the damage caused to
14 another, regularly harbors, keeps, or exercises control over the dog, but does
15 not include a person who, at the time of the damage, is temporarily harboring,
16 keeping, or exercising control over the dog.
17 (3) “Running at large” means a dog goes uncontrolled by the dog’s
18 owner upon the premises of another without the consent of the owner of the
19 premises or of another person authorized to give consent or goes uncontrolled
20 by the owner upon a highway, public road, street, or any other place open to
21 the public generally.
